# Suspec — append to a CODE repo's .gitignore. The Suspec workspace commits its
# specs, tasks, reviews, and findings; only code-repo scratch is ignored here.

# Agent scratch and transient task hand-offs
.agents/tmp/
tmp/

# Local state of the future Suspec CLI (machine state, never committed)
.suspec/

# Backups `suspec update --write` leaves when it replaces a customized kit file (reconcile, then delete).
*.suspec-bak
*.suspec-bak.*

# Generated agent definitions (`suspec agents emit --codex`) — regenerate from the source defs, never commit.
.codex/

# Isolated task worktrees (`suspec worktree create` puts them here, inside the repo) — committing one
# stages an embedded gitlink, never what you want.
.worktrees/

# If this workspace is CO-LOCATED with your code (the same repo holds specs/ and the app), add your
# language's build/cache ignores too, or `suspec review` will flag committed bytecode/artifacts as
# out-of-scope changes. Common ones (uncomment what applies):
#   __pycache__/   *.py[cod]        # Python
#   node_modules/  dist/            # Node
#   target/                         # Rust / JVM
#   *.sqlite3      *.db             # local SQLite databases
